ign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Simple enough</span><hr size=1> Well, Verant apparently sees wizzies as:<br>
- Direct Damage (we can't do as much damage as a melee type over the long run, but we can do quite a lot of damage very quickly - cheetah vs. lion type thing)<br>
- Teleporters (its a convenience for us to be able to hop around the world and take other people there)<br>
- AE (we can do the most damage in the game in a properly configured group)<br>
<br>
Problem:<br>
<br>
We aren't usually wanted in groups (pre-50).  Our AE power only works in specialized groups of several wizzies, a chanter, cleric and a puller.  That group rakes in the XP, but it's rare.  Porting does nothing to make us wanted in groups and with most single/double pull groups, our DD makes us a weak version of a meleer, though we do shorten the battle.<br>
<br>
My proposal to make us more desirable to groups is simple - an enhancement to our ability to Evac: A single spell (lv34-44 for 500 mana) that lets us summon a group member to the wizard for the same cost as a portal.  This is the same as the Mage spell &quot;Call of the Hero&quot;, only without the agro clearance and the added ability to bring them from wherever they are (in any zone).<br>
<br>
Presto: we can now evac out of anywhere and get the group back inside in a (fairly) short time.  <br>
<br>
This doesn't compete with mages; they can't use CoH to bring peeps from another zone - CoH is a hate-reducing spell or one to get somebody who is just inside zone. It *does* sound a bit like a cleric Revive (lv29) - essentially bring a party member to caster from another zone with no XP gain.  Thats why I'm putting it at least at 34, most likely 39 or 44 and upping the mana cost from 300 (for revive) to 500.  Doesn't have the exploitability of group portal to bind point (can't drop a ton of whoop-ass on a nasty mob by surprise since the wiz has to go there first and summon one at a time).  To reduce this possibility even more, put like a 10-second recast time on it too.  The main reason I dont use evac much is because the warrior types dont want to run back from wherever the closest portal point is.  With this fix, we could become every group's &quot;Panic Button&quot;  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
And other things as long as I'm fixing wizzies:<br>
<br>
DD Enhancement:<br>
<br>
- Add a real damage spell at lv20 (Force Shock can't be chain cast - wizzies have to use a wussy lv16 spell until lv24!).  Since there is a new ice based at 24 and fire at 29, I would make this a fire based Bolt-type spell.  100 mana, 165 max damage.<br>
<br>
- Lose the spiral line of spells and replace them with a long-cast-time, very-long-reload time (1 hour) series of nasty nukes (This has already been proposed).  Even keep the name of the spell, the mana and the fact that they must be researched, just change the amount of damage and make it DD instead of AE spiral.  Was Akbor a total wuss?  What did he have against columns to want to make a marginally-wider range AE for a chunk more mana?  Lets make his line of spells honor his supposed great power... <br>
<br>
Here's how I'd replace the spirals with the new line:<br>
<br>
Lv12 Frost Spiral (max 44 damage, 100 mana) -&gt; Frost Blast (max 160 damage)<br>
Lv20 Fire Spiral (max 76 damage, 150 mana) -&gt; Fire Blast (max 300 damage)<br>
Lv29 Shock Spiral (max 118 damage, 200 mana) -&gt; Lightning Blast (max 450)<br>
Lv39 Force Spiral (max 172 damage+interrupt, 250 mana) -&gt; Force Blast (max 800+interrupt)<br>
<br>
The Lv49 spell could be left a spiral rather than make its damage in line with the other Blast spells (which would make it more powerful than ice comet).  If we want to go replace the entire line, I'd make it:<br>
<br>
Lv49 Wrath of AlKabor (max ??, 500 mana) -&gt; Elemental Blast (max 1000 fire damage)<br>
<br>
So generally, that makes each Akbor spell do a little more damage than the DD 2 spell levels higher.  Its actually about the same damage as the spiral spell hitting four targets, just condensed into one shot.  This can't be exploited due to the 1 hour recast delay, as well as the fact that the resist rate isn't changed - cast this on a mob too high above your level and it fails just as badly as your other spells.  <br>
<br>
This makes it a great Emergency spell to whack that nasty add that attacked when the party was mostly dead,  or to help put dent in a big mob...  It increases our long term damage potential.  If they still sound too powerful, make it also use a pricey component.  Say 5pp per level of Blast spell; so Frost uses a 5pp gem, Fire 10pp, Lightning 15pp, Force 20pp and Elemental 25pp.<br>
<br>
TP Enhancement:<br>
<br>
Why is the West Gate spell location like, 20 feet away from the North Gate?<br>
Put the pyramid close to the barbarian village on the west side of the zone.<br>
<br>
I'm sure I'm just dreaming here...<br>
<br>
<br>
The meganuke enhancements wouldn't be hard to code at all, since the game engine is already set up to handle damage, long recast times and components.  The summon-to-caster variant would require extensive changes though, since you cannot currently target any object or player outside the zone.  To make it easier on Verant's beleagured programmers:<br>
<br>
Make it a Translocate: Bind spell that sends the player from the same zone as the caster to the casters bind point.  <br>
<br>
This is less balanced and more dangerous.  With summon-to-caster, the wizzie has to go to the zone first and can't walk up to a nasty mob and start pulling people in.  TL: Bind would let the caster just send an advance party ahead and stay behind in safety until everyone was there.  Also, this could be used to send people into unpleasant situations - &quot;oh  sure, I'm bound in Firiona, I'll send you there!&quot; and send them to the bottom of the hole or something.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Just my 2 cp.. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showPrevMessage?topicID=340.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showNextMessage?topicID=340.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=340.topic&index=0><img src=http://www.graffe.com/messageboard/add_reply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.emailToFriend?topicID=340.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.threadControl?topicID=340.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=340.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=340.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub23.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="graffeswizardcompilationfrm1">General Discussion<option value="graffeswizardcompilationfrm41">Interface Design<option value="graffeswizardcompilationfrm40">Poster Made Polls<option value="graffeswizard